<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Responsive Image Implementation Examples</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Responsive Image Implementation Examples for AKM SecureKey</h1>
    
    <h2>1. Hero Section Background (CSS)</h2>
    <pre><code>
/* Current */
.hero-section {
    background-image: url('assets/hero-banner.png');
}

/* Optimized with responsive images */
.hero-section {
    background-image: url('assets/optimized/hero-banner-mobile.jpg');
}

@media (min-width: 640px) {
    .hero-section {
        background-image: url('assets/optimized/hero-banner-small.jpg');
    }
}

@media (min-width: 1280px) {
    .hero-section {
        background-image: url('assets/optimized/hero-banner-medium.jpg');
    }
}

@media (min-width: 1920px) {
    .hero-section {
        background-image: url('assets/optimized/hero-banner-large.jpg');
    }
}

/* With WebP support detection */
.webp .hero-section {
    background-image: url('assets/optimized/hero-banner-mobile.webp');
}
    </code></pre>

    <h2>2. Industry Card Images</h2>
    <pre><code>
<!-- Current -->
&lt;img src="assets/industries/industries-energy.png" alt="Energy Industry" class="w-full h-48 object-cover"&gt;

<!-- Optimized -->
&lt;picture&gt;
    &lt;source type="image/webp" 
            srcset="assets/optimized/industries-energy-small.webp 640w,
                    assets/optimized/industries-energy-medium.webp 1280w,
                    assets/optimized/industries-energy-large.webp 1920w"
            sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, (max-width: 1024px) 50vw, 33vw"&gt;
    &lt;img src="assets/optimized/industries-energy-large.jpg" 
         alt="Energy Industry"
         class="w-full h-48 object-cover"
         srcset="assets/optimized/industries-energy-small.jpg 640w,
                 assets/optimized/industries-energy-medium.jpg 1280w,
                 assets/optimized/industries-energy-large.jpg 1920w"
         sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, (max-width: 1024px) 50vw, 33vw"
         loading="lazy"&gt;
&lt;/picture&gt;
    </code></pre>

    <h2>3. Industry Photo Images</h2>
    <pre><code>
<!-- Current -->
&lt;img src="assets/industries/industries-energy-photo.png" alt="Energy Industry Operations" class="w-full h-full object-cover shadow-lg"&gt;

<!-- Optimized (these are already small, just convert format) -->
&lt;picture&gt;
    &lt;source type="image/webp" srcset="assets/optimized/industries-energy-photo.webp"&gt;
    &lt;img src="assets/optimized/industries-energy-photo.jpg" 
         alt="Energy Industry Operations" 
         class="w-full h-full object-cover shadow-lg"
         loading="lazy"&gt;
&lt;/picture&gt;
    </code></pre>

    <h2>4. Logo (Remove Duplicate)</h2>
    <pre><code>
<!-- Update all references from -->
&lt;img src="assets/logos/akmlogo-white.png" ...&gt;

<!-- To -->
&lt;img src="assets/akmlogo-white.png" ...&gt;
    </code></pre>

    <h2>5. Add WebP Detection Script</h2>
    <pre><code>
&lt;script&gt;
// Add to the head of your HTML
function checkWebP(callback) {
    var webP = new Image();
    webP.onload = webP.onerror = function () {
        callback(webP.height == 2);
    };
    webP.src = "data:image/webp;base64,UklGRjoAAABXRUJQVlA4IC4AAACyAgCdASoCAAIALmk0mk0iIiIiIgBoSygABc6WWgAA/veff/0PP8bA//LwYAAA";
}

checkWebP(function(support) {
    if(support) {
        document.documentElement.classList.add('webp');
    } else {
        document.documentElement.classList.add('no-webp');
    }
});
&lt;/script&gt;
    </code></pre>

    <h2>Implementation Steps</h2>
    <ol>
        <li>Run image optimization script to create optimized versions</li>
        <li>Update CSS background images with media queries</li>
        <li>Replace &lt;img&gt; tags with &lt;picture&gt; elements</li>
        <li>Add loading="lazy" to images below the fold</li>
        <li>Remove duplicate logo file and update references</li>
        <li>Test on various devices and browsers</li>
    </ol>

    <h2>Benefits</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>70-80% reduction in image file sizes</li>
        <li>Faster page load times, especially on mobile</li>
        <li>Better user experience with appropriate image sizes</li>
        <li>Reduced bandwidth usage</li>
        <li>Improved SEO and Core Web Vitals scores</li>
    </ul>
